---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import StatusLight from "../components/StatusLight.astro";
---

<Layout pageTitle="About Me">
  <section class="about">
    <!-- Profile -->
    <div class="profile">
      <p class="prompt">$ cat ~/about.md</p>
      <h1 class="name">Solomon Neas</h1>
      <p class="role">Infrastructure Engineer · Security Builder · AI Toolsmith</p>

      <div class="profile-details">
        <div class="detail">
          <span class="detail-label">[LOCATION]</span>
          <span class="detail-value">Central Florida</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail">
          <span class="detail-label">[STATUS]</span>
          <span class="detail-value green"><StatusLight status="ongoing" /> Building things that actually work</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail">
          <span class="detail-label">[EDUCATION]</span>
          <span class="detail-value">M.S. Cybersecurity Intelligence @ USF · B.A.S. · A.S. NSET</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail">
          <span class="detail-label">[PREVIOUS LIFE]</span>
          <span class="detail-value">Executive Chef (17 years)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <div class="section">
      <p class="summary">
        I grew up one of ten kids, troubleshooting DOS while my friends were still figuring out
        Windows 95. Spent 17 years in professional kitchens. Now I build SOC platforms and
        infrastructure tooling. The path doesn't make sense until you walk it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Timeline -->
    <div class="section">
      <p class="section-header">$ cat /var/log/history.log</p>
      <p class="section-comment">// It makes sense if you don't think about it too hard</p>

      <div class="timeline">
        <!-- Chapter 1 -->
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="entry-header">
              <span class="entry-date">~1995-2005</span>
              <span class="entry-title">EARLY_TECH_INIT</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              My dad was a chemical engineer and software developer. He had me understanding the
              significance of C and C++ before middle school, and I became the family IT department
              by default. Ten kids, one person who could fix the computer. You do the math.
            </p>
            <p>
              That turned into a web design hustle during the GeoCities and Angelfire era. Custom sites,
              PHP migrations, helping people claim their corner of the early web. Also ran a side gig
              building and repairing PCs. Learned hardware from the ground up because I couldn't
              afford not to.
            </p>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">DOS</span>
              <span class="tag">HTML</span>
              <span class="tag">PHP</span>
              <span class="tag">Hardware</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chapter 2 -->
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="entry-header">
              <span class="entry-date">2005-2021</span>
              <span class="entry-title">CULINARY_DETOUR</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              Life happened. For 17 years I worked as a cook and eventually an executive chef. My best
              year was $40K working 80-hour weeks doing prep, service, and management for kitchens
              that burned through staff like they burned through butter. It sounds like a completely
              different career until you realize kitchens and server rooms run on the same thing:
              controlled chaos, troubleshooting under pressure, and knowing when something is about
              to break before it does.
            </p>
            <p>
              I managed teams, optimized workflows, handled vendor relationships, and ran operations
              for a 140-student facility. When COVID shut my kitchen down in 2020, I looked at my
              resume and thought: "I've been meaning to get out of the kitchen for years. Perfect timing."
            </p>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Leadership</span>
              <span class="tag">Operations</span>
              <span class="tag">Crisis Management</span>
              <span class="tag">17 Years of "Why Am I Still Doing This"</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chapter 3 -->
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="entry-header">
              <span class="entry-date">2021-2024</span>
              <span class="entry-title">THREE_DEGREES_FIVE_YEARS</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              Enrolled at Polk State College with 21% of a degree I'd started in high school. Drove
              four hours round trip daily to attend classes in person. Finished an A.S. in Network Systems
              Engineering Technology, then a B.A.S. in Supervision and Management, while working as
              a lab assistant making $17 an hour doing the work of a full infrastructure team.
            </p>
            <p>
              During that time, I migrated the department from VMware to Proxmox (saving $68K/year
              in licensing), built a full SOC stack from scratch for students to train on, designed
              lab environments, and automated just about everything that wasn't nailed down. The
              department got $3 million for AI and cybersecurity. I got a pat on the back and a
              blocked promotion. So it goes.
            </p>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Proxmox</span>
              <span class="tag">VMware Migration</span>
              <span class="tag">SOC Architecture</span>
              <span class="tag">Active Directory</span>
              <span class="tag">4hr Daily Commute</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chapter 4 -->
        <div class="timeline-entry current">
          <div class="timeline-marker active"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="entry-header">
              <span class="entry-date">2025-PRESENT</span>
              <span class="entry-title">CURRENT_STATE</span>
              <StatusLight status="ongoing" />
            </div>
            <p>
              Finishing my M.S. in Cybersecurity Intelligence at USF while building the tools I
              actually want to use. I run multi-agent AI pipelines that scaffold, build, review, and
              deploy projects in parallel. I write MCP servers that let AI assistants talk to Wazuh,
              TheHive, MISP, and FortiGate. I build dashboards that turn Zeek logs and Suricata
              alerts into something a human can actually parse at 2 AM.
            </p>
            <p>
              The through-line from kitchens to infrastructure to security to AI isn't obvious, but
              it's there: take something messy and chaotic, build systems around it, make it
              repeatable, and teach other people how to run it without you. That's the whole job,
              whether you're plating 200 covers or hunting threats across a 200-endpoint network.
            </p>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Agentic AI</span>
              <span class="tag">MCP Servers</span>
              <span class="tag">Threat Hunting</span>
              <span class="tag">Security Tooling</span>
              <span class="tag">Multi-Model Pipelines</span>
              <span class="tag">Still Learning</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Skills -->
    <div class="section">
      <p class="section-header">$ cat ~/skills.json</p>
      <div class="skills-grid">
        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-label">Infrastructure</h3>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Proxmox VE</span>
            <span class="tag">Active Directory</span>
            <span class="tag">Samba</span>
            <span class="tag">Docker</span>
            <span class="tag">10G Networking</span>
            <span class="tag">LACP</span>
            <span class="tag">Linux Administration</span>
            <span class="tag">Windows Server</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-label">Security</h3>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Wazuh</span>
            <span class="tag">TheHive / Cortex</span>
            <span class="tag">MISP</span>
            <span class="tag">Zeek</span>
            <span class="tag">Suricata</span>
            <span class="tag">Palo Alto</span>
            <span class="tag">FortiGate</span>
            <span class="tag">MITRE ATT&CK</span>
            <span class="tag">Threat Hunting</span>
            <span class="tag">SIGMA Rules</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-label">Development</h3>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">React</span>
            <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
            <span class="tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tag">FastAPI</span>
            <span class="tag">Astro</span>
            <span class="tag">Node.js</span>
            <span class="tag">MCP Servers</span>
            <span class="tag">REST APIs</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-label">AI & Automation</h3>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Multi-Agent Orchestration</span>
            <span class="tag">Claude / GPT / Gemini</span>
            <span class="tag">Prompt Engineering</span>
            <span class="tag">Local LLMs (Ollama)</span>
            <span class="tag">Agentic Pipelines</span>
            <span class="tag">Code Review Automation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="section nav-section">
      <p class="section-comment">// Continue exploring</p>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/experience" class="nav-link">$ cd /experience</a>
        <a href="/projects" class="nav-link">$ cd /projects</a>
        <a href="/hire" class="nav-link">$ cd /hire</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="terminal-footer">
      <span class="cursor-blink">█</span> EOF
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Profile */
  .profile {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 15%, transparent);
  }

  .prompt {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.4;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .name {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: #10b981;
  }

  .role {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(0.85rem, 2vw, 1rem);
    opacity: 0.65;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .profile-details {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .detail {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .detail-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    opacity: 0.45;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    min-width: 100px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .detail-value {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .detail-value.green {
    color: #10b981;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  /* Summary */
  .summary {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    opacity: 0.85;
    max-width: 58ch;
    text-align: left;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section-header {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .section-comment {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.45;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 6px;
    top: 8px;
    bottom: 8px;
    width: 1px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 15%, transparent);
  }

  .timeline-entry {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline-entry:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: -2rem;
    top: 6px;
    width: 13px;
    height: 13px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 25%, transparent);
    background: var(--background, #fff2d1);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .timeline-marker.active {
    border-color: #10b981;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 20%, transparent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 30%, transparent);
  }

  .timeline-content {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 3%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent);
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .timeline-content:hover {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 20%, transparent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 5%, transparent);
  }

  .timeline-entry.current .timeline-content {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 25%, transparent);
  }

  .entry-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .entry-date {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #10b981;
  }

  .entry-title {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .timeline-content p {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    opacity: 0.8;
    max-width: 58ch;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .timeline-content p:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Tags */
  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tag {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 5%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent);
    border-radius: 3px;
    opacity: 0.7;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* Skills Grid */
  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .skill-group {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 3%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .skill-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    color: #10b981;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  /* Nav */
  .nav-section {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 15%, transparent);
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .nav-link {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    opacity: 0.6;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .nav-link:hover {
    opacity: 1;
    color: #10b981;
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 30%, transparent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 5%, transparent);
  }

  /* Footer */
  .terminal-footer {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .cursor-blink {
    animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }

  @keyframes blink {
    from, to { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .name {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .detail {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.15rem;
    }

    .detail-label {
      min-width: auto;
    }

    .timeline {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .timeline-marker {
      left: -1.5rem;
    }

    .skills-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .nav-links {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
